573 template<typename T> bool builtin_isinf(T arg)
574 {
575 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CMATH
576 return std::isinf(arg);
577 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
578 return !::_finite(static_cast<double>(arg)) && !::_isnan(static_cast<double>(arg));
579 #else
580 return arg == std::numeric_limits<T>::infinity() || arg == -std::numeric_limits<T>::infinity();
581 #endif
582 }
583
589 template<typename T> bool builtin_isnan(T arg)
590 {
591 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CMATH
592 return std::isnan(arg);
593 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
594 return ::_isnan(static_cast<double>(arg)) != 0;
595 #else
596 return arg != arg;
597 #endif
598 }
599
605 template<typename T> bool builtin_signbit(T arg)
606 {
607 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CMATH
608 return std::signbit(arg);
609 #else
610 return arg < T() || (arg == T() && T(1)/arg < T());
611 #endif
612 }

618 inline uint32 sign_mask(uint32 arg)
619 {
620 static const int N = std::numeric_limits<uint32>::digits - 1;
621 #if HALF_TWOS_COMPLEMENT_INT
622 return static_cast<int32>(arg) >> N;
623 #else
624 return -((arg>>N)&1);
625 #endif
626 }
627
632 inline uint32 arithmetic_shift(uint32 arg, int i)
633 {
634 #if HALF_TWOS_COMPLEMENT_INT
635 return static_cast<int32>(arg) >> i;
636 #else
637 return static_cast<int32>(arg)/(static_cast<int32>(1)<<i) - ((arg>>(std::numeric_limits<uint32>::digits-1))&1);
638 #endif
639 }

647 inline int& errflags() { HALF_THREAD_LOCAL int flags = 0; return flags; }
648
652 inline void raise(int HALF_UNUSED_NOERR(flags), bool HALF_UNUSED_NOERR(cond) = true)
653 {
654 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
655 if(!cond)
656 return;
657 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING_FLAGS
658 errflags() |= flags;
659 #endif
660 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING_ERRNO
661 if(flags & FE_INVALID)
662 errno = EDOM;
663 else if(flags & (FE_DIVBYZERO|FE_OVERFLOW|FE_UNDERFLOW))
664 errno = ERANGE;
665 #endif
666 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING_FENV && HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CFENV
667 std::feraiseexcept(flags);
668 #endif
669 #ifdef HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_INVALID
670 if(flags & FE_INVALID)
671 HALF_THROW_DOMAIN_ERROR(HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_INVALID);
672 #endif
673 #ifdef HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_DIVBYZERO
674 if(flags & FE_DIVBYZERO)
675 HALF_THROW_DOMAIN_ERROR(HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_DIVBYZERO);
676 #endif
677 #ifdef HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_OVERFLOW
678 if(flags & FE_OVERFLOW)
679 HALF_THROW_OVERFLOW_ERROR(HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_OVERFLOW);
680 #endif
681 #ifdef HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_UNDERFLOW
682 if(flags & FE_UNDERFLOW)
683 HALF_THROW_UNDERFLOW_ERROR(HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_UNDERFLOW);
684 #endif
685 #ifdef HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_INEXACT
686 if(flags & FE_INEXACT)
687 HALF_THROW_RANGE_ERROR(HALF_ERRHANDLING_THROW_INEXACT);
688 #endif
689 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING_UNDERFLOW_TO_INEXACT
690 if((flags & FE_UNDERFLOW) && !(flags & FE_INEXACT))
691 raise(FE_INEXACT);
692 #endif
693 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING_OVERFLOW_TO_INEXACT
694 if((flags & FE_OVERFLOW) && !(flags & FE_INEXACT))
695 raise(FE_INEXACT);
696 #endif
697 #endif
698 }

706 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR bool compsignal(unsigned int x, unsigned int y)
707 {
708 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
709 raise(FE_INVALID, (x&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 || (y&0x7FFF)>0x7C00);
710 #endif
711 return (x&0x7FFF) > 0x7C00 || (y&0x7FFF) > 0x7C00;
712 }

718 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int signal(unsigned int nan)
719 {
720 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
721 raise(FE_INVALID, !(nan&0x200));
722 #endif
723 return nan | 0x200;
724 }

731 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int signal(unsigned int x, unsigned int y)
732 {
733 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
734 raise(FE_INVALID, ((x&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 && !(x&0x200)) || ((y&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 && !(y&0x200)));
735 #endif
736 return ((x&0x7FFF)>0x7C00) ? (x|0x200) : (y|0x200);
737 }
738
745 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int signal(unsigned int x, unsigned int y, unsigned int z)
746 {
747 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
748 raise(FE_INVALID, ((x&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 && !(x&0x200)) || ((y&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 && !(y&0x200)) || ((z&0x7FFF)>0x7C00 && !(z&0x200)));
749 #endif
750 return ((x&0x7FFF)>0x7C00) ? (x|0x200) : ((y&0x7FFF)>0x7C00) ? (y|0x200) : (z|0x200);
751 }

758 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int select(unsigned int x, unsigned int HALF_UNUSED_NOERR(y))
759 {
760 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
761 return (((y&0x7FFF)>0x7C00) && !(y&0x200)) ? signal(y) : x;
762 #else
763 return x;
764 #endif
765 }

794 inline HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int check_underflow(unsigned int arg)
795 {
796 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING && !HALF_ERRHANDLING_UNDERFLOW_TO_INEXACT
797 raise(FE_UNDERFLOW, !(arg&0x7C00));
798 #endif
799 return arg;
800 }
801
805
811 template<std::float_round_style R> HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int overflow(unsigned int sign = 0)
812 {
813 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
814 raise(FE_OVERFLOW);
815 #endif
816 return (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (sign+0x7C00-(sign>>15)) :
817 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (sign+0x7BFF+(sign>>15)) :
818 (R==std::round_toward_zero) ? (sign|0x7BFF) :
819 (sign|0x7C00);
820 }
821
827 template<std::float_round_style R> HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int underflow(unsigned int sign = 0)
828 {
829 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
830 raise(FE_UNDERFLOW);
831 #endif
832 return (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (sign+1-(sign>>15)) :
833 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (sign+(sign>>15)) :
834 sign;
835 }
836
847 template<std::float_round_style R,bool I> HALF_CONSTEXPR_NOERR unsigned int rounded(unsigned int value, int g, int s)
848 {
849 #if HALF_ERRHANDLING
850 value += (R==std::round_to_nearest) ? (g&(s|value)) :
851 (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (~(value>>15)&(g|s)) :
852 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? ((value>>15)&(g|s)) : 0;
853 if((value&0x7C00) == 0x7C00)
854 raise(FE_OVERFLOW);
855 else if(value & 0x7C00)
856 raise(FE_INEXACT, I || (g|s)!=0);
857 else
858 raise(FE_UNDERFLOW, !(HALF_ERRHANDLING_UNDERFLOW_TO_INEXACT) || I || (g|s)!=0);
859 return value;
860 #else
861 return (R==std::round_to_nearest) ? (value+(g&(s|value))) :
862 (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (value+(~(value>>15)&(g|s))) :
863 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (value+((value>>15)&(g|s))) :
864 value;
865 #endif
866 }

876 template<std::float_round_style R,bool E,bool I> unsigned int integral(unsigned int value)
877 {
878 unsigned int abs = value & 0x7FFF;
879 if(abs < 0x3C00)
880 {
881 raise(FE_INEXACT, I);
882 return ((R==std::round_to_nearest) ? (0x3C00&-static_cast<unsigned>(abs>=(0x3800+E))) :
883 (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (0x3C00&-(~(value>>15)&(abs!=0))) :
884 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (0x3C00&-static_cast<unsigned>(value>0x8000)) :
885 0) | (value&0x8000);
886 }
887 if(abs >= 0x6400)
888 return (abs>0x7C00) ? signal(value) : value;
889 unsigned int exp = 25 - (abs>>10), mask = (1<<exp) - 1;
890 raise(FE_INEXACT, I && (value&mask));
891 return (( (R==std::round_to_nearest) ? ((1<<(exp-1))-(~(value>>exp)&E)) :
892 (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (mask&((value>>15)-1)) :
893 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (mask&-(value>>15)) :
894 0) + value) & ~mask;
895 }

911 template<std::float_round_style R,unsigned int F,bool S,bool N,bool I> unsigned int fixed2half(uint32 m, int exp = 14, unsigned int sign = 0, int s = 0)
912 {
913 if(S)
914 {
915 uint32 msign = sign_mask(m);
916 m = (m^msign) - msign;
917 sign = msign & 0x8000;
918 }
919 if(N)
920 for(; m<(static_cast<uint32>(1)<<F) && exp; m<<=1,--exp) ;
921 else if(exp < 0)
922 return rounded<R,I>(sign+(m>>(F-10-exp)), (m>>(F-11-exp))&1, s|((m&((static_cast<uint32>(1)<<(F-11-exp))-1))!=0));
923 return rounded<R,I>(sign+(exp<<10)+(m>>(F-10)), (m>>(F-11))&1, s|((m&((static_cast<uint32>(1)<<(F-11))-1))!=0));
924 }

1070 template<std::float_round_style R,typename T> unsigned int float2half_impl(T value, ...)
1071 {
1072 unsigned int hbits = static_cast<unsigned>(builtin_signbit(value)) << 15;
1073 if(value == T())
1074 return hbits;
1075 if(builtin_isnan(value))
1076 return hbits | 0x7FFF;
1077 if(builtin_isinf(value))
1078 return hbits | 0x7C00;
1079 int exp;
1080 std::frexp(value, &exp);
1081 if(exp > 16)
1082 return overflow<R>(hbits);
1083 if(exp < -13)
1084 value = std::ldexp(value, 25);
1085 else
1086 {
1087 value = std::ldexp(value, 12-exp);
1088 hbits |= ((exp+13)<<10);
1089 }
1090 T ival, frac = std::modf(value, &ival);
1091 int m = std::abs(static_cast<int>(ival));
1092 return rounded<R,false>(hbits+(m>>1), m&1, frac!=T());
1093 }

1303 inline double half2float_impl(unsigned int value, double, true_type)
1304 {
1305 #if HALF_ENABLE_F16C_INTRINSICS
1306 return _mm_cvtsd_f64(_mm_cvtps_pd(_mm_cvtph_ps(_mm_cvtsi32_si128(value))));
1307 #elif HALF_ENABLE_NEON_INTRINSICS
1308 auto hbits = static_cast<uint16_t>(value);
1309 float16_t h;
1310 std::memcpy(&h, &hbits, sizeof(float16_t));
1311 return static_cast<double>(h);
1312 #else
1313 uint32 hi = static_cast<uint32>(value&0x8000) << 16;
1314 unsigned int abs = value & 0x7FFF;
1315 if(abs)
1316 {
1317 hi |= 0x3F000000 << static_cast<unsigned>(abs>=0x7C00);
1318 for(; abs<0x400; abs<<=1,hi-=0x100000) ;
1319 hi += static_cast<uint32>(abs) << 10;
1320 }
1321 bits<double>::type dbits = static_cast<bits<double>::type>(hi) << 32;
1322 double out;
1323 std::memcpy(&out, &dbits, sizeof(double));
1324 return out;
1325 #endif
1326 }

1332 template<typename T> T half2float_impl(unsigned int value, T, ...)
1333 {
1334 T out;
1335 unsigned int abs = value & 0x7FFF;
1336 if(abs > 0x7C00)
1337 out = (std::numeric_limits<T>::has_signaling_NaN && !(abs&0x200)) ? std::numeric_limits<T>::signaling_NaN() :
1338 std::numeric_limits<T>::has_quiet_NaN ? std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN() : T();
1339 else if(abs == 0x7C00)
1340 out = std::numeric_limits<T>::has_infinity ? std::numeric_limits<T>::infinity() : (std::numeric_limits<T>::max)();
1341 else if(abs > 0x3FF)
1342 out = std::ldexp(static_cast<T>((abs&0x3FF)|0x400), (abs>>10)-25);
1343 else
1344 out = std::ldexp(static_cast<T>(abs), -24);
1345 return (value&0x8000) ? -out : out;
1346 }

1353 {
1354 return half2float_impl(value, T(), bool_type<std::numeric_limits<T>::is_iec559&&sizeof(typename bits<T>::type)==sizeof(T)>());
1355 }

1366 template<std::float_round_style R,bool E,bool I,typename T> T half2int(unsigned int value)
1367 {
1368 unsigned int abs = value & 0x7FFF;
1369 if(abs >= 0x7C00)
1370 {
1371 raise(FE_INVALID);
1372 return (value&0x8000) ? (std::numeric_limits<T>::min)() : (std::numeric_limits<T>::max)();
1373 }
1374 if(abs < 0x3800)
1375 {
1376 raise(FE_INEXACT, I);
1377 return (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? T(~(value>>15)&(abs!=0)) :
1378 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? -T(value>0x8000) :
1379 T();
1380 }
1381 int exp = 25 - (abs>>10);
1382 unsigned int m = (value&0x3FF) | 0x400;
1383 int32 i = static_cast<int32>((exp<=0) ? (m<<-exp) : ((m+(
1384 (R==std::round_to_nearest) ? ((1<<(exp-1))-(~(m>>exp)&E)) :
1385 (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? (((1<<exp)-1)&((value>>15)-1)) :
1386 (R==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (((1<<exp)-1)&-(value>>15)) : 0))>>exp));
1387 if((!std::numeric_limits<T>::is_signed && (value&0x8000)) || (std::numeric_limits<T>::digits<16 &&
1388 ((value&0x8000) ? (-i<(std::numeric_limits<T>::min)()) : (i>(std::numeric_limits<T>::max)()))))
1389 raise(FE_INVALID);
1390 else if(I && exp > 0 && (m&((1<<exp)-1)))
1391 raise(FE_INEXACT);
1392 return static_cast<T>((value&0x8000) ? -i : i);
1393 }

1404 template<std::float_round_style R> uint32 mulhi(uint32 x, uint32 y)
1405 {
1406 uint32 xy = (x>>16) * (y&0xFFFF), yx = (x&0xFFFF) * (y>>16), c = (xy&0xFFFF) + (yx&0xFFFF) + (((x&0xFFFF)*(y&0xFFFF))>>16);
1407 return (x>>16)*(y>>16) + (xy>>16) + (yx>>16) + (c>>16) +
1408 ((R==std::round_to_nearest) ? ((c>>15)&1) : (R==std::round_toward_infinity) ? ((c&0xFFFF)!=0) : 0);
1409 }

1429 inline uint32 divide64(uint32 x, uint32 y, int &s)
1430 {
1431 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_LONG_LONG
1432 unsigned long long xx = static_cast<unsigned long long>(x) << 32;
1433 return s = (xx%y!=0), static_cast<uint32>(xx/y);
1434 #else
1435 y >>= 1;
1436 uint32 rem = x, div = 0;
1437 for(unsigned int i=0; i<32; ++i)
1438 {
1439 div <<= 1;
1440 if(rem >= y)
1441 {
1442 rem -= y;
1443 div |= 1;
1444 }
1445 rem <<= 1;
1446 }
1447 return s = rem > 1, div;
1448 #endif
1449 }

1458 template<bool Q,bool R> unsigned int mod(unsigned int x, unsigned int y, int *quo = NULL)
1459 {
1460 unsigned int q = 0;
1461 if(x > y)
1462 {
1463 int absx = x, absy = y, expx = 0, expy = 0;
1464 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--expx) ;
1465 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--expy) ;
1466 expx += absx >> 10;
1467 expy += absy >> 10;
1468 int mx = (absx&0x3FF) | 0x400, my = (absy&0x3FF) | 0x400;
1469 for(int d=expx-expy; d; --d)
1470 {
1471 if(!Q && mx == my)
1472 return 0;
1473 if(mx >= my)
1474 {
1475 mx -= my;
1476 q += Q;
1477 }
1478 mx <<= 1;
1479 q <<= static_cast<int>(Q);
1480 }
1481 if(!Q && mx == my)
1482 return 0;
1483 if(mx >= my)
1484 {
1485 mx -= my;
1486 ++q;
1487 }
1488 if(Q)
1489 {
1490 q &= (1<<(std::numeric_limits<int>::digits-1)) - 1;
1491 if(!mx)
1492 return *quo = q, 0;
1493 }
1494 for(; mx<0x400; mx<<=1,--expy) ;
1495 x = (expy>0) ? ((expy<<10)|(mx&0x3FF)) : (mx>>(1-expy));
1496 }
1497 if(R)
1498 {
1499 unsigned int a, b;
1500 if(y < 0x800)
1501 {
1502 a = (x<0x400) ? (x<<1) : (x+0x400);
1503 b = y;
1504 }
1505 else
1506 {
1507 a = x;
1508 b = y - 0x400;
1509 }
1510 if(a > b || (a == b && (q&1)))
1511 {
1512 int exp = (y>>10) + (y<=0x3FF), d = exp - (x>>10) - (x<=0x3FF);
1513 int m = (((y&0x3FF)|((y>0x3FF)<<10))<<1) - (((x&0x3FF)|((x>0x3FF)<<10))<<(1-d));
1514 for(; m<0x800 && exp>1; m<<=1,--exp) ;
1515 x = 0x8000 + ((exp-1)<<10) + (m>>1);
1516 q += Q;
1517 }
1518 }
1519 if(Q)
1520 *quo = q;
1521 return x;
1522 }

1529 template<unsigned int F> uint32 sqrt(uint32 &r, int &exp)
1530 {
1531 int i = exp & 1;
1532 r <<= i;
1533 exp = (exp-i) / 2;
1534 uint32 m = 0;
1535 for(uint32 bit=static_cast<uint32>(1)<<F; bit; bit>>=2)
1536 {
1537 if(r < m+bit)
1538 m >>= 1;
1539 else
1540 {
1541 r -= m + bit;
1542 m = (m>>1) + bit;
1543 }
1544 }
1545 return m;
1546 }

1553 inline uint32 exp2(uint32 m, unsigned int n = 32)
1554 {
1555 static const uint32 logs[] = {
1556 0x80000000, 0x4AE00D1D, 0x2934F098, 0x15C01A3A, 0x0B31FB7D, 0x05AEB4DD, 0x02DCF2D1, 0x016FE50B,
1557 0x00B84E23, 0x005C3E10, 0x002E24CA, 0x001713D6, 0x000B8A47, 0x0005C53B, 0x0002E2A3, 0x00017153,
1558 0x0000B8AA, 0x00005C55, 0x00002E2B, 0x00001715, 0x00000B8B, 0x000005C5, 0x000002E3, 0x00000171,
1559 0x000000B9, 0x0000005C, 0x0000002E, 0x00000017, 0x0000000C, 0x00000006, 0x00000003, 0x00000001 };
1560 if(!m)

1653 inline uint32 angle_arg(unsigned int abs, int &k)
1654 {
1655 uint32 m = (abs&0x3FF) | ((abs>0x3FF)<<10);
1656 int exp = (abs>>10) + (abs<=0x3FF) - 15;
1657 if(abs < 0x3A48)
1658 return k = 0, m << (exp+20);
1659 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_LONG_LONG
1660 unsigned long long y = m * 0xA2F9836E4E442, mask = (1ULL<<(62-exp)) - 1, yi = (y+(mask>>1)) & ~mask, f = y - yi;
1661 uint32 sign = -static_cast<uint32>(f>>63);
1662 k = static_cast<int>(yi>>(62-exp));
1663 return (multiply64(static_cast<uint32>((sign ? -f : f)>>(31-exp)), 0xC90FDAA2)^sign) - sign;
1664 #else

1667 k = static_cast<int>(yi>>(30-exp));

1669 return (multiply64((exp>-1) ? (((fh<<(1+exp))&0xFFFFFFFF)|((fl&0xFFFFFFFF)>>(31-exp))) : fh, 0xC90FDAA2)^sign) - sign;
1670 #endif

1676 inline std::pair<uint32,uint32> atan2_args(unsigned int abs)
1677 {
1678 int exp = -15;
1679 for(; abs<0x400; abs<<=1,--exp) ;
1680 exp += abs >> 10;

1683 r = 0x40000000 - ((rexp>-31) ? ((r>>-rexp)|((r&((static_cast<uint32>(1)<<-rexp)-1))!=0)) : 1);
1684 for(rexp=0; r<0x40000000; r<<=1,--rexp) ;
1685 uint32 mx = sqrt<30>(r, rexp);
1686 int d = exp - rexp;
1687 if(d < 0)
1688 return std::make_pair((d<-14) ? ((my>>(-d-14))+((my>>(-d-15))&1)) : (my<<(14+d)), (mx<<14)+(r<<13)/mx);
1689 if(d > 0)
1690 return std::make_pair(my<<14, (d>14) ? ((mx>>(d-14))+((mx>>(d-15))&1)) : ((d==14) ? mx : ((mx<<(14-d))+(r<<(13-d))/mx)));
1691 return std::make_pair(my<<13, (mx<<13)+(r<<12)/mx);

1699 inline std::pair<uint32,uint32> hyperbolic_args(unsigned int abs, int &exp, unsigned int n = 32)

1707 }

1718 my |= s;

1838 {
1839 int abs = arg & 0x7FFF, expx = (abs>>10) + (abs<=0x3FF) - 15, expy = -15, ilog, i;
1840 uint32 mx = static_cast<uint32>((abs&0x3FF)|((abs>0x3FF)<<10)) << 20, my, r;
1841 for(; abs<0x400; abs<<=1,--expy) ;
1842 expy += abs >> 10;

1844 r *= r;
1845 i = r >> 31;

1847 r >>= i;

1851 {
1852 r = 0x40000000 + ((expy>-30) ? ((r>>-expy)|((r&((static_cast<uint32>(1)<<-expy)-1))!=0)) : 1);
1853 expy = 0;
1854 }
1855 else
1856 {
1857 r += 0x40000000 >> expy;
1858 i = r >> 31;
1859 r = (r>>i) | (r&i);
1860 expy += i;
1861 }
1862 }
1863 else

1872 mx >>= expy - expx;
1873 ilog = expy;
1874 }
1875 else
1876 {
1877 my >>= expx - expy;
1878 ilog = expx;
1879 }
1880 my += mx;
1881 i = my >> 31;
1882 static const int G = S && (R==std::round_to_nearest);

2592 inline half operator+(half x, half y)
2593 {
2594 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
2595 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_)+detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_)));
2596 #else
2597 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF;
2598 bool sub = ((x.data_^y.data_)&0x8000) != 0;
2599 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
2600 return half(detail::binary, (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00) ? detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_) : (absy!=0x7C00) ? x.data_ :
2601 (sub && absx==0x7C00) ? detail::invalid() : y.data_);
2602 if(!absx)
2603 return absy ? y : half(detail::binary, (half::round_style==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (x.data_|y.data_) : (x.data_&y.data_));
2604 if(!absy)
2605 return x;
2606 unsigned int sign = ((sub && absy>absx) ? y.data_ : x.data_) & 0x8000;
2607 if(absy > absx)
2608 std::swap(absx, absy);
2609 int exp = (absx>>10) + (absx<=0x3FF), d = exp - (absy>>10) - (absy<=0x3FF), mx = ((absx&0x3FF)|((absx>0x3FF)<<10)) << 3, my;
2610 if(d < 13)
2611 {
2612 my = ((absy&0x3FF)|((absy>0x3FF)<<10)) << 3;
2613 my = (my>>d) | ((my&((1<<d)-1))!=0);
2614 }
2615 else
2616 my = 1;
2617 if(sub)
2618 {
2619 if(!(mx-=my))
2620 return half(detail::binary, static_cast<unsigned>(half::round_style==std::round_toward_neg_infinity)<<15);
2621 for(; mx<0x2000 && exp>1; mx<<=1,--exp) ;
2622 }
2623 else
2624 {
2625 mx += my;
2626 int i = mx >> 14;
2627 if((exp+=i) > 30)
2628 return half(detail::binary, detail::overflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2629 mx = (mx>>i) | (mx&i);
2630 }
2631 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,false>(sign+((exp-1)<<10)+(mx>>3), (mx>>2)&1, (mx&0x3)!=0));
2632 #endif
2633 }

2658 inline half operator*(half x, half y)
2659 {
2660 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
2661 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_)*detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_)));
2662 #else
2663 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, exp = -16;
2664 unsigned int sign = (x.data_^y.data_) & 0x8000;
2665 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
2666 return half(detail::binary, (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00) ? detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_) :
2667 ((absx==0x7C00 && !absy)||(absy==0x7C00 && !absx)) ? detail::invalid() : (sign|0x7C00));
2668 if(!absx || !absy)
2669 return half(detail::binary, sign);
2670 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--exp) ;
2671 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--exp) ;
2672 detail::uint32 m = static_cast<detail::uint32>((absx&0x3FF)|0x400) * static_cast<detail::uint32>((absy&0x3FF)|0x400);
2673 int i = m >> 21, s = m & i;
2674 exp += (absx>>10) + (absy>>10) + i;
2675 if(exp > 29)
2676 return half(detail::binary, detail::overflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2677 else if(exp < -11)
2678 return half(detail::binary, detail::underflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2679 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,20,false,false,false>(m>>i, exp, sign, s));
2680 #endif
2681 }

2691 inline half operator/(half x, half y)
2692 {
2693 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
2694 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_)/detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_)));
2695 #else
2696 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, exp = 14;
2697 unsigned int sign = (x.data_^y.data_) & 0x8000;
2698 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
2699 return half(detail::binary, (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00) ? detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_) :
2700 (absx==absy) ? detail::invalid() : (sign|((absx==0x7C00) ? 0x7C00 : 0)));
2701 if(!absx)
2702 return half(detail::binary, absy ? sign : detail::invalid());
2703 if(!absy)
2704 return half(detail::binary, detail::pole(sign));
2705 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--exp) ;
2706 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,++exp) ;
2707 detail::uint32 mx = (absx&0x3FF) | 0x400, my = (absy&0x3FF) | 0x400;
2708 int i = mx < my;
2709 exp += (absx>>10) - (absy>>10) - i;
2710 if(exp > 29)
2711 return half(detail::binary, detail::overflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2712 else if(exp < -11)
2713 return half(detail::binary, detail::underflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2714 mx <<= 12 + i;
2715 my <<= 1;
2716 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,11,false,false,false>(mx/my, exp, sign, mx%my!=0));
2717 #endif
2718 }

2784 {

2786 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)

2824 inline half remquo(half x, half y, int *quo)
2825 {
2826 unsigned int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, value = x.data_ & 0x8000;
2827 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
2828 return half(detail::binary, (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00) ? detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_) :
2829 (absx==0x7C00) ? detail::invalid() : (*quo = 0, x.data_));

2832 bool qsign = ((value^y.data_)&0x8000) != 0;
2833 int q = 1;

2836 return *quo = qsign ? -q : q, half(detail::binary, value);

2849 inline half fma(half x, half y, half z)
2850 {
2851 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
2852 detail::internal_t fx = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_), fy = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_), fz = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(z.data_);
2853 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CMATH && FP_FAST_FMA
2854 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::fma(fx, fy, fz)));
2855 #else
2856 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(fx*fy+fz));
2857 #endif
2858 #else
2859 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, absz = z.data_ & 0x7FFF, exp = -15;
2860 unsigned int sign = (x.data_^y.data_) & 0x8000;
2861 bool sub = ((sign^z.data_)&0x8000) != 0;
2862 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00 || absz >= 0x7C00)
2863 return (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00 || absz>0x7C00) ? half(detail::binary, detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_, z.data_)) :
2864 (absx==0x7C00) ? half(detail::binary, (!absy || (sub && absz==0x7C00)) ? detail::invalid() : (sign|0x7C00)) :
2865 (absy==0x7C00) ? half(detail::binary, (!absx || (sub && absz==0x7C00)) ? detail::invalid() : (sign|0x7C00)) : z;
2866 if(!absx || !absy)
2867 return absz ? z : half(detail::binary, (half::round_style==std::round_toward_neg_infinity) ? (z.data_|sign) : (z.data_&sign));
2868 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--exp) ;
2869 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--exp) ;
2870 detail::uint32 m = static_cast<detail::uint32>((absx&0x3FF)|0x400) * static_cast<detail::uint32>((absy&0x3FF)|0x400);
2871 int i = m >> 21;
2872 exp += (absx>>10) + (absy>>10) + i;
2873 m <<= 3 - i;
2874 if(absz)
2875 {
2876 int expz = 0;
2877 for(; absz<0x400; absz<<=1,--expz) ;
2878 expz += absz >> 10;
2879 detail::uint32 mz = static_cast<detail::uint32>((absz&0x3FF)|0x400) << 13;
2880 if(expz > exp || (expz == exp && mz > m))
2881 {
2882 std::swap(m, mz);
2883 std::swap(exp, expz);
2884 if(sub)
2885 sign = z.data_ & 0x8000;
2886 }
2887 int d = exp - expz;
2888 mz = (d<23) ? ((mz>>d)|((mz&((static_cast<detail::uint32>(1)<<d)-1))!=0)) : 1;
2889 if(sub)
2890 {
2891 m = m - mz;
2892 if(!m)
2893 return half(detail::binary, static_cast<unsigned>(half::round_style==std::round_toward_neg_infinity)<<15);
2894 for(; m<0x800000; m<<=1,--exp) ;
2895 }
2896 else
2897 {
2898 m += mz;
2899 i = m >> 24;
2900 m = (m>>i) | (m&i);
2901 exp += i;
2902 }
2903 }
2904 if(exp > 30)
2905 return half(detail::binary, detail::overflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2906 else if(exp < -10)
2907 return half(detail::binary, detail::underflow<half::round_style>(sign));
2908 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,23,false,false,false>(m, exp-1, sign));
2909 #endif
2910 }

3271 #else
3272 unsigned int abs = arg.data_ & 0x7FFF, bias = 0x4000;
3273 if(!abs || arg.data_ >= 0x7C00)

3275 detail::invalid() : !abs ? detail::pole(arg.data_&0x8000) : 0);
3276 for(; abs<0x400; abs<<=1,bias-=0x400) ;

3279 return half(detail::binary, 0x7A00-(abs>>1));

3282 return pow(arg, half(detail::binary, 0xB800));

3284 int expy = (f>>11) - 31, expx = 32 - (abs>>10), i = mz >> 21;
3285 for(mz=0x60000000-(((mz>>i)*mx)>>(expx-2*expy-i)); mz<0x40000000; mz<<=1,--expy) ;
3286 i = (my*=mz>>10) >> 31;
3287 expy += i;
3288 my = (my>>(20+i)) + 1;
3289 i = (mz=my*my) >> 21;
3290 for(mz=0x60000000-(((mz>>i)*mx)>>(expx-2*expy-i)); mz<0x40000000; mz<<=1,--expy) ;
3291 i = (my*=(mz>>10)+1) >> 31;

3355 inline half hypot(half x, half y)
3356 {
3357 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3358 detail::internal_t fx = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_), fy = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_);
3359 #if HALF_ENABLE_CPP11_CMATH
3360 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::hypot(fx, fy)));
3361 #else
3362 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::sqrt(fx*fx+fy*fy)));
3363 #endif
3364 #else
3365 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, expx = 0, expy = 0;
3366 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
3367 return half(detail::binary, (absx==0x7C00) ? detail::select(0x7C00, y.data_) :
3368 (absy==0x7C00) ? detail::select(0x7C00, x.data_) : detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_));
3369 if(!absx)
3370 return half(detail::binary, absy ? detail::check_underflow(absy) : 0);
3371 if(!absy)
3372 return half(detail::binary, detail::check_underflow(absx));
3373 if(absy > absx)
3374 std::swap(absx, absy);
3375 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--expx) ;
3376 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--expy) ;
3377 detail::uint32 mx = (absx&0x3FF) | 0x400, my = (absy&0x3FF) | 0x400;
3378 mx *= mx;
3379 my *= my;
3380 int ix = mx >> 21, iy = my >> 21;
3381 expx = 2*(expx+(absx>>10)) - 15 + ix;
3382 expy = 2*(expy+(absy>>10)) - 15 + iy;
3383 mx <<= 10 - ix;
3384 my <<= 10 - iy;
3385 int d = expx - expy;
3386 my = (d<30) ? ((my>>d)|((my&((static_cast<detail::uint32>(1)<<d)-1))!=0)) : 1;
3387 return half(detail::binary, detail::hypot_post<half::round_style>(mx+my, expx));
3388 #endif
3389 }

3427 for(; absz<0x400; absz<<=1,--expz) ;

3454 #endif

3467 inline half pow(half x, half y)
3468 {
3469 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3470 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::pow(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_), detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_))));
3471 #else
3472 int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, exp = -15;
3473 if(!absy || x.data_ == 0x3C00)
3474 return half(detail::binary, detail::select(0x3C00, (x.data_==0x3C00) ? y.data_ : x.data_));
3475 bool is_int = absy >= 0x6400 || (absy>=0x3C00 && !(absy&((1<<(25-(absy>>10)))-1)));
3476 unsigned int sign = x.data_ & (static_cast<unsigned>((absy<0x6800)&&is_int&&((absy>>(25-(absy>>10)))&1))<<15);
3477 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
3478 return half(detail::binary, (absx>0x7C00 || absy>0x7C00) ? detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_) :

3480 (0x7C00&-((y.data_>>15)^(absx>0x3C00)))) : (sign|(0x7C00&((y.data_>>15)-1U))));
3481 if(!absx)
3482 return half(detail::binary, (y.data_&0x8000) ? detail::pole(sign) : sign);
3483 if((x.data_&0x8000) && !is_int)
3484 return half(detail::binary, detail::invalid());
3485 if(x.data_ == 0xBC00)
3486 return half(detail::binary, sign|0x3C00);
3487 switch(y.data_)
3488 {
3489 case 0x3800: return sqrt(x);
3490 case 0x3C00: return half(detail::binary, detail::check_underflow(x.data_));
3491 case 0x4000: return x * x;
3492 case 0xBC00: return half(detail::binary, 0x3C00) / x;
3493 }
3494 for(; absx<0x400; absx<<=1,--exp) ;
3495 detail::uint32 ilog = exp + (absx>>10), msign = detail::sign_mask(ilog), f, m =
3496 (((ilog<<27)+((detail::log2(static_cast<detail::uint32>((absx&0x3FF)|0x400)<<20)+8)>>4))^msign) - msign;
3497 for(exp=-11; m<0x80000000; m<<=1,--exp) ;
3498 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--exp) ;
3499 m = detail::multiply64(m, static_cast<detail::uint32>((absy&0x3FF)|0x400)<<21);
3500 int i = m >> 31;
3501 exp += (absy>>10) + i;
3502 m <<= 1 - i;
3503 if(exp < 0)
3504 {
3505 f = m >> -exp;
3506 exp = 0;
3507 }
3508 else
3509 {
3510 f = (m<<exp) & 0x7FFFFFFF;
3511 exp = m >> (31-exp);
3512 }
3513 return half(detail::binary, detail::exp2_post<half::round_style>(f, exp, ((msign&1)^(y.data_>>15))!=0, sign));
3514 #endif
3515 }

3531 inline void sincos(half arg, half *sin, half *cos)
3532 {
3533 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3534 detail::internal_t f = detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(arg.data_);
3535 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::sin(f)));
3536 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::cos(f)));
3537 #else
3538 int abs = arg.data_ & 0x7FFF, sign = arg.data_ >> 15, k;
3539 if(abs >= 0x7C00)
3540 *sin = *cos = half(detail::binary, (abs==0x7C00) ? detail::invalid() : detail::signal(arg.data_));
3541 else if(!abs)
3542 {
3543 *sin = arg;
3544 *cos = half(detail::binary, 0x3C00);
3545 }
3546 else if(abs < 0x2500)
3547 {
3548 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(arg.data_-1, 1, 1));
3549 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(0x3BFF, 1, 1));
3550 }
3551 else
3552 {
3553 if(half::round_style != std::round_to_nearest)
3554 {
3555 switch(abs)
3556 {
3557 case 0x48B7:
3558 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((~arg.data_&0x8000)|0x1D07, 1, 1));
3559 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(0xBBFF, 1, 1));
3560 return;
3561 case 0x598C:
3562 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((arg.data_&0x8000)|0x3BFF, 1, 1));
3563 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(0x80FC, 1, 1));
3564 return;
3565 case 0x6A64:
3566 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((~arg.data_&0x8000)|0x3BFE, 1, 1));
3567 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(0x27FF, 1, 1));
3568 return;
3569 case 0x6D8C:
3570 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((arg.data_&0x8000)|0x0FE6, 1, 1));
3571 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(0x3BFF, 1, 1));
3572 return;
3573 }
3574 }
3575 std::pair<detail::uint32,detail::uint32> sc = detail::sincos(detail::angle_arg(abs, k), 28);
3576 switch(k & 3)
3577 {
3578 case 1: sc = std::make_pair(sc.second, -sc.first); break;
3579 case 2: sc = std::make_pair(-sc.first, -sc.second); break;
3580 case 3: sc = std::make_pair(-sc.second, sc.first); break;
3581 }
3582 *sin = half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,30,true,true,true>((sc.first^-static_cast<detail::uint32>(sign))+sign));
3583 *cos = half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,30,true,true,true>(sc.second));
3584 }
3585 #endif
3586 }

3596 inline half sin(half arg)
3597 {
3598 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3599 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::sin(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(arg.data_))));
3600 #else
3601 int abs = arg.data_ & 0x7FFF, k;
3602 if(!abs)
3603 return arg;
3604 if(abs >= 0x7C00)
3605 return half(detail::binary, (abs==0x7C00) ? detail::invalid() : detail::signal(arg.data_));
3606 if(abs < 0x2900)
3607 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(arg.data_-1, 1, 1));
3608 if(half::round_style != std::round_to_nearest)
3609 switch(abs)
3610 {
3611 case 0x48B7: return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((~arg.data_&0x8000)|0x1D07, 1, 1));
3612 case 0x6A64: return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((~arg.data_&0x8000)|0x3BFE, 1, 1));
3613 case 0x6D8C: return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((arg.data_&0x8000)|0x0FE6, 1, 1));
3614 }
3615 std::pair<detail::uint32,detail::uint32> sc = detail::sincos(detail::angle_arg(abs, k), 28);
3616 detail::uint32 sign = -static_cast<detail::uint32>(((k>>1)&1)^(arg.data_>>15));
3617 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,30,true,true,true>((((k&1) ? sc.second : sc.first)^sign) - sign));
3618 #endif

3658 {
3659 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3660 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::tan(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(arg.data_))));
3661 #else
3662 int abs = arg.data_ & 0x7FFF, exp = 13, k;
3663 if(!abs)
3664 return arg;
3665 if(abs >= 0x7C00)
3666 return half(detail::binary, (abs==0x7C00) ? detail::invalid() : detail::signal(arg.data_));
3667 if(abs < 0x2700)
3668 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(arg.data_, 0, 1));
3669 if(half::round_style != std::round_to_nearest)
3670 switch(abs)

3672 case 0x658C: return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((arg.data_&0x8000)|0x07E6, 1, 1));
3673 case 0x7330: return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>((~arg.data_&0x8000)|0x4B62, 1, 1));
3674 }
3675 std::pair<detail::uint32,detail::uint32> sc = detail::sincos(detail::angle_arg(abs, k), 30);
3676 if(k & 1)
3677 sc = std::make_pair(-sc.second, sc.first);
3678 detail::uint32 signy = detail::sign_mask(sc.first), signx = detail::sign_mask(sc.second);
3679 detail::uint32 my = (sc.first^signy) - signy, mx = (sc.second^signx) - signx;
3680 for(; my<0x80000000; my<<=1,--exp) ;
3681 for(; mx<0x80000000; mx<<=1,++exp) ;
3682 return half(detail::binary, detail::tangent_post<half::round_style>(my, mx, exp, (signy^signx^arg.data_)&0x8000));
3683 #endif

3778 inline half atan2(half y, half x)
3779 {
3780 #ifdef HALF_ARITHMETIC_TYPE
3781 return half(detail::binary, detail::float2half<half::round_style>(std::atan2(detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(y.data_), detail::half2float<detail::internal_t>(x.data_))));
3782 #else
3783 unsigned int absx = x.data_ & 0x7FFF, absy = y.data_ & 0x7FFF, signx = x.data_ >> 15, signy = y.data_ & 0x8000;
3784 if(absx >= 0x7C00 || absy >= 0x7C00)
3785 {
3786 if(absx > 0x7C00 || absy > 0x7C00)
3787 return half(detail::binary, detail::signal(x.data_, y.data_));
3788 if(absy == 0x7C00)
3789 return half(detail::binary, (absx<0x7C00) ? detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x3E48, 0, 1) :
3790 signx ? detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x40B6, 0, 1) :
3791 detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x3A48, 0, 1));
3792 return (x.data_==0x7C00) ? half(detail::binary, signy) : half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x4248, 0, 1));
3793 }
3794 if(!absy)
3795 return signx ? half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x4248, 0, 1)) : y;
3796 if(!absx)
3797 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x3E48, 0, 1));
3798 int d = (absy>>10) + (absy<=0x3FF) - (absx>>10) - (absx<=0x3FF);
3799 if(d > (signx ? 18 : 12))
3800 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x3E48, 0, 1));
3801 if(signx && d < -11)
3802 return half(detail::binary, detail::rounded<half::round_style,true>(signy|0x4248, 0, 1));
3803 if(!signx && d < ((half::round_style==std::round_toward_zero) ? -15 : -9))
3804 {
3805 for(; absy<0x400; absy<<=1,--d) ;
3806 detail::uint32 mx = ((absx<<1)&0x7FF) | 0x800, my = ((absy<<1)&0x7FF) | 0x800;
3807 int i = my < mx;
3808 d -= i;
3809 if(d < -25)
3810 return half(detail::binary, detail::underflow<half::round_style>(signy));
3811 my <<= 11 + i;
3812 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,11,false,false,true>(my/mx, d+14, signy, my%mx!=0));
3813 }
3814 detail::uint32 m = detail::atan2( ((absy&0x3FF)|((absy>0x3FF)<<10))<<(19+((d<0) ? d : (d>0) ? 0 : -1)),
3815 ((absx&0x3FF)|((absx>0x3FF)<<10))<<(19-((d>0) ? d : (d<0) ? 0 : 1)));
3816 return half(detail::binary, detail::fixed2half<half::round_style,31,false,true,true>(signx ? (0xC90FDAA2-m) : m, 15, signy, signx));
3817 #endif
3818 }
